The system orchestrator — stage 1 of the pipeline. Accepts raw text and turns it into a traced compression job.

# lang Go {#go_lang}

Go 1.26, standard library only, `gofmt`-formatted. One `main` package, built with `go build`. No goroutines — the orchestrator is a single linear pass.

# good Idiomatic Go {#go_patterns}

- Every error is handled explicitly at the call site; no `_`-discarded errors.
- JSON marshalling goes through struct types with explicit `json:"snake_case"` tags — never `map[string]interface{}` for outbound messages.
- A single deferred recovery in `main` converts any panic into the shared error envelope before the process exits.

# dep {#go_deps}

Go standard library only. Nothing in `go.mod` beyond the module declaration.
